Proof. We provide a constructive proof via hierarchi cal tensor network embedding. The strategy is to build a Multi-scale Entanglement Renormalization Ansatz (MERA)-like structure with scale-dependent branching and bond dimensions tuned to achieve the target entropy scaling. 
Step 1: Hierarchical construction. Divide the lattice into hierarchical scales s = 0, 1, . . . , S with S = ⌈log2 L⌉. At scale s, introduce ns tensor nodes with: 
• Branching number: bs = ⌈sγ⌉ for γ > 0, 
• Bond dimension: χs = χ0sηfor η > 0. 
