C. Transport properties 
Anomalous diffusion emerges naturally. For conserved quantities, the diffusion exponent z relating length and time scales ℓ ∼ t1/z is modified from the conventional z = 2 to z < 2, potentially approaching ballistic transport z = 1 depending on the strength of nonlocality. 
VII. NUMERICAL SIMULATIONS 
We validate the theoretical predictions through numer ical experiments. 
A. Tensor network simulation 
We implemented a simplified 1D tensor network with L = 64 sites, depth S = 6, and branching bs = s1.5, bond dimension χs = 4s. Figure 1 shows entanglement entropy S(ℓ) versus subsystem size ℓ. 
